The paper deals with valued constraint satisfaction problems (VCSPs), which are a fundamental topic in computer science and artificial intelligence. The paper presents a constructive characterization of the power of linear programming for solving VCSPs, which is a topic that falls under the categories of algorithms and complexity (cs.DS, cs.CC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
